content: Waste of money, buggy and unreliable!

Am I crazy or are some images misclassified? On some tests I'm going very slow and double checking and still sometimes get 90%. The memory game is also slightly buggy in that you can sometimes get 3 or more tiles flipped at once (which shouldn't be possible). I'm still skeptical of the overall science here. I've also ordered one of the workbooks to go along with the app. Hopefully it describes more about the exercises (how long to do, how often, etc). Will update my review after using more.
The application just randomly stops working in the middle of sessions. I have not been able to use it for my CRPS.
Quite limited for the money. It only assist you with the first stage of graded motor imagery.

app shuts down regularly. have uninstalled and reinstalled likely 20 times in the past 5 weeks. makes it VERY difficult for my physiotherapist to track everything. please make the appropriate corrections or recommendations.

downloaded the app. Will NOT open!!! No word yet from developer..Very unhappy..can't even get the app store to refund so I could try again. My OT recommended this...now can't use it. too bad!! Mary-Anne
has lots of potential but the app keeps crashing!!
sqlite error. Didn't work for me.

Several of the answers given seem to be wrong - which doesn't help with the aims of this app. I took the time to provide evidence to the developer but sadly he/she did not respond therefore I can only assume that despite this being a paid for app, there is no support. The app also suffers from other functionality bugs too. Overall a disappointing and frustrating experience. Update: Since the Dec 18 update it now crashes in results/options section. Sigh
App shuts down when trying to export data
I was using the app in conjunction with my OT as l try to get on top of CRPS but now l can't export my results to the OT which is incredibly disappointing

While this app achieves it's purpose and is relatively easy to use, it's quite buggy. After receiving a phone call whilst playing, the game firstly didn't pause, then the app was almost impossible to exit from and after I managed to get out of it, it kept opening up on it's own and was really hard to exit from each time it opened. I had to uninstall it to get it to stop.

Easy to use.   I was immediately hooked and played for ages. ..and i don't do games normally!  Immediate and relevant feedback. A great little tool for pain treatment as well as cognitive function.   Thanks noisters
